  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal Profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed across all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors. Seven factors were formally assessed; six remain flagged as epistemic gaps. All assessed factors achieved required credibility levels under the Minimal profile declaration. Intended use is restricted to pre-clinical regulatory submission supporting 510(k) substantial equivalence argumentation for rotary blood pump hemolysis under nominal VAD operating conditions (flow 4–6 L/min, speed 2400–3200 RPM). Decision: Accepted under Minimal profile.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/vad-cfd-hemolysis-absolute-prediction-class3",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-hemolysis-v2",
